    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stacks or packets of small gold squares which have been removed from the "shoders" packets and cut into smaller pieces, interleaved with fine goldbeater's skin, the whole then being bound with parchment strips. The stacks are beaten again by hand to produce gold leaf.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000044672/Barnes, Gilding (1962)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De derde fase van de productie van bladgoud met de hand; stapels kleine gouden vierkantjes, die uit de ’shoders’ komen en in kleinere stukken zijn gesneden, met tussen de bladen goudslagersvlies en bij elkaar gebonden met perkamentstroken. De stapeltjes worden vervolgens met de hand platgeslagen om bladgoud te maken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Als Teil der dritten Stufe der manuellen Blattgoldproduktion: Stapel kleiner Goldquadrate, die von der "Lotform" entfernt und in kleinere Stücke geschnitten wurden, durchschossen mit feiner Goldschlägerhaut; das Ganze wird dann mit Pergamentstreifen gebunden. Die Stapel werden von Hand geschlagen, um Blattgold herzustellen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在手工打製金箔的第三階段中，將堆疊的小型黃金方塊自「包金膜」(shoder) 取出，切割成更小片，插入金箔匠用的質地細緻之牛腸膜將之隔開，之後以羊皮紙條捆住整疊，用手敲擊疊片，以製造金箔。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
